1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:38.030
<b>Forces of Rage</b>

3
00:01:36.340 --> 00:01:38.450
Luffy.

4
00:01:38.450 --> 00:01:40.620
Are you really gonna wait here?!

5
00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:43.120
We're in the middle of enemy territory.

6
00:01:46.910 --> 00:01:48.550
I'll wait!

7
00:01:48.550 --> 00:01:53.550
According to Pound... the people who
took down a sweet commander...

8
00:01:53.550 --> 00:01:56.500
were annihilated in no time flat

9
00:01:56.500 --> 00:02:00.590
by Big Mom's vengeful army
that came along with a storm.

10
00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:03.680
So the enemy will come...

11
00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:05.680
but Sanji-kun...

12
00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:07.900
Sanji will come!

13
00:02:07.900 --> 00:02:11.190
So, I'll wait here!

14
00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:21.090
Crap! My head has been completely trimmed...

15
00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:33.790
What's going on?!

16
00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:37.630
It was clear, but suddenly,
dark clouds started gathering...

17
00:02:40.010 --> 00:02:42.320
What's wrong, Kingbaum?!

18
00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:47.470
That mountain is Whole Cake Chateau,
Mama's residence!

19
00:02:47.470 --> 00:02:49.440
Mama is furious!

20
00:02:51.020 --> 00:02:52.810
Big Mom is?!

21
00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:55.860
But...

22
00:02:57.130 --> 00:02:58.890
No...

23
00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:03.490
No way...

24
00:03:03.490 --> 00:03:05.830
You've got to be kidding!

25
00:03:06.490 --> 00:03:09.500
Is this the power of one person?!

26
00:03:13.210 --> 00:03:17.090
Linlin is always accompanied
by weather elements.

27
00:03:17.710 --> 00:03:22.180
Nothing can stop her when she gets mad.

28
00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:37.210
<b>Sweet City</b>

29
00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:46.990
Master Prometheus and Master Zeus
are running wild!

30
00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:53.140
Mama... She's outraged!

31
00:04:46.240 --> 00:04:50.970
Clear the way!
The enraged army is passing through!

32
00:04:50.970 --> 00:04:54.230
An army to avenge Minister Cracker
has been mobilized!

33
00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:56.350
Move! Get out of the way!

34
00:05:08.840 --> 00:05:11.000
Look how many there are!

35
00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:15.350
Seems like they're gonna go
after Straw Hat to kill him.

36
00:05:20.180 --> 00:05:24.880
If I remember right,
he said he'd be there waiting for you.

37
00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:29.890
This is it for him!

38
00:05:32.850 --> 00:05:36.390
I can't believe it!
That's Bobbin "the Disposer"!

39
00:05:37.830 --> 00:05:40.020
"Mad Moiselle" Amande!

40
00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:43.730
Oh! That's Mont d'Or "the Scribe"!

41
00:05:43.730 --> 00:05:47.340
I wonder how much
the total of their bounties is?!

42
00:05:58.120 --> 00:06:01.230
I'll be waiting right here!

43
00:06:05.550 --> 00:06:08.850
Well, I'm guessing that captain 
isn't so dumb that

44
00:06:08.850 --> 00:06:11.260
he'd see that battalion and stick around.

45
00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:37.910
It started raining.

46
00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:44.210
No...

47
00:06:44.210 --> 00:06:46.550
this is... syrup.

48
00:06:49.220 --> 00:06:52.530
I'm not gonna let even syrup in my mouth!

49
00:06:52.530 --> 00:06:55.640
I won't eat anything other than
what Sanji cooks!

50
00:06:57.140 --> 00:07:00.310
<b>Whole Cake Chateau</b>

51
00:07:07.280 --> 00:07:09.360
Oh, there's Mama! Mama!

52
00:07:09.360 --> 00:07:11.950
– Mama!
– Mama!

53
00:07:13.910 --> 00:07:16.660
Are you all being good?

54
00:07:16.660 --> 00:07:18.770
Mama, Mama!

55
00:07:18.770 --> 00:07:20.620
What is it, Anana?

56
00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:25.880
The head chef won't let me use a knife.
I wanna cut my stuffed animal.

57
00:07:25.880 --> 00:07:28.510
Oh, no!

58
00:07:28.510 --> 00:07:32.340
Dolce, Dragée,
go and borrow one for her.

59
00:07:32.340 --> 00:07:37.500
No, Mama! Once Anana has a knife,
she'll pop our balloons!

60
00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:41.140
Yeah! She's bad!
I'm gonna kill her someday!

61
00:07:42.480 --> 00:07:46.190
We shouldn't say those things, right, Mama?

62
00:07:47.790 --> 00:07:53.240
Everyone has 100 to 200 people
that they want to kill.

63
00:07:53.240 --> 00:07:55.950
Be nice to each other, my children.

64
00:07:55.950 --> 00:08:00.330
We'll have Big Sis Pudding's
wedding tomorrow!

65
00:08:00.330 --> 00:08:03.110
Are you excited?

66
00:08:04.710 --> 00:08:09.050
You get to eat a delicious wedding cake.

67
00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:11.010
Yay! Yay!

68
00:08:11.010 --> 00:08:13.260
Now let's meet...

69
00:08:13.260 --> 00:08:15.970
the groom's family!

70
00:08:15.970 --> 00:08:19.280
♪ Door! ♪

71
00:08:26.980 --> 00:08:30.810
It's good to have you here, Germa 66.

72
00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:32.490
Sorry to be late.

73
00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:35.570
Emperor... Big Mom!

74
00:08:35.570 --> 00:08:40.830
We ran into a little problem,
but everything should be fine now.

75
00:08:51.050 --> 00:08:53.950
Oh, Pudding! There you are.

76
00:08:53.950 --> 00:08:55.430
Sorry for being late.

77
00:09:01.640 --> 00:09:05.560
Anyway, I've heard a lot about him.

78
00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:10.650
Your son's a cook, huh?
He's perfect for Pudding.

79
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:14.610
Well, it doesn't matter even if he's not.

80
00:09:14.610 --> 00:09:17.320
It's a political marriage.

81
00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:23.450
As long as you and I share mutual interests,
that's all that matters, Judge!

82
00:09:25.980 --> 00:09:31.880
Yeah, but it'd be nice
if our children are happy.

83
00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:36.720
Let's have a nice wedding tomorrow!

84
00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:39.450
Yes, let's.

85
00:09:58.410 --> 00:10:01.600
♪ Tea! ♪

86
00:09:59.280 --> 00:10:01.600
♪ Green tea! ♪

87
00:10:01.600 --> 00:10:03.660
♪ What would you like to have? ♪

88
00:10:04.660 --> 00:10:06.210
Tea.

89
00:10:07.660 --> 00:10:10.220
♪ Tea! Tea! Tea! Tea! ♪

90
00:10:10.220 --> 00:10:12.590
♪ Tea! ♪

91
00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:23.470
♪ Eat us! Eat us! ♪

92
00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:20.800
♪ Start with me! ♪

93
00:10:22.300 --> 00:10:23.470
♪ You can have me too! ♪

94
00:10:23.470 --> 00:10:25.880
♪ You need lots of honey, young man! ♪

95
00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:28.470
♪ It's very... ♪

96
00:10:28.470 --> 00:10:31.520
♪ sweet! ♪

97
00:10:31.520 --> 00:10:42.060
♪ La la lunch! ♪

98
00:10:36.480 --> 00:10:37.980
♪ Sausage! ♪

99
00:10:37.320 --> 00:10:37.980
♪ Cabbage! ♪

100
00:10:37.840 --> 00:10:40.700
♪ La la lunch! ♪ ♪ Ham! ♪

101
00:10:38.820 --> 00:10:40.700
♪ Pancake! ♪

102
00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:44.820
♪ Delicious! ♪
♪ La la lunch! ♪

103
00:10:44.820 --> 00:10:46.950
Could you pipe down?

104
00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:48.460
What?!

105
00:10:48.460 --> 00:10:49.830
♪ Don't say such a thing! ♪

106
00:10:49.830 --> 00:10:52.330
♪ Let's have a delicious lunch! ♪

107
00:10:52.330 --> 00:11:02.960
♪ La la lunch! ♪

108
00:10:56.640 --> 00:10:59.390
It's so noisy!

109
00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:02.180
♪ How do I taste? ♪

110
00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:08.020
♪ La la lunch! ♪

111
00:11:02.180 --> 00:11:04.890
♪ Am I good? ♪

112
00:11:06.740 --> 00:11:17.060
♪ La la lunch! ♪

113
00:11:11.900 --> 00:11:14.310
S... Sanji-san...

114
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:29.080
♪ La la lunch! ♪

115
00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:31.690
"I need to talk to you
in private later."

116
00:11:37.210 --> 00:11:40.220
<b>Outside Sweet City</b>

117
00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:43.140
<b>Team Luffy</b>

118
00:12:02.660 --> 00:12:04.450
Oh, no...

119
00:12:04.450 --> 00:12:06.960
Oh, no!

120
00:12:07.750 --> 00:12:10.330
How many... are there?!

121
00:12:27.110 --> 00:12:29.060
Luffy...

122
00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:39.860
Luffy! Please! Hide yourself at least!

123
00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:43.000
It's okay to get away from here, even for a bit!

124
00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:44.360
No!

125
00:12:44.910 --> 00:12:48.120
Sanji might come while I'm gone!

126
00:12:48.120 --> 00:12:50.790
You guys, back up a little!

127
00:12:50.790 --> 00:12:52.700
Don't do it, Luffy! It's impossible!

128
00:12:52.700 --> 00:12:55.420
Don't you know whose territory we're in?!

129
00:13:18.820 --> 00:13:21.020
That's a big army...

130
00:13:21.020 --> 00:13:22.820
You can't beat it!

131
00:13:25.360 --> 00:13:27.740
We found Straw Hat Luffy!

132
00:13:34.540 --> 00:13:37.000
I promised him...

133
00:13:40.660 --> 00:13:43.170
that I'd be here waiting!

134
00:13:50.050 --> 00:13:53.060
<b>Inside
Whole Cake Chateau</b>

135
00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:53.640
You led Luffy and the others to this island?

136
00:13:53.640 --> 00:13:55.160
I'm sorry!

137
00:13:57.100 --> 00:14:01.380
I promised them that I'd bring Sanji-san
to the southwest coast.

138
00:13:57.140 --> 00:14:00.330
<b>Pudding's Room</b>

139
00:14:01.380 --> 00:14:06.240
But I couldn't keep my word,
and now they're in danger because of me.

140
00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:09.080
I see.

141
00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:15.000
I was wondering how they made it through
the sea under so much surveillance.

142
00:14:15.460 --> 00:14:19.170
Now I understand. But...

143
00:14:19.170 --> 00:14:22.730
I wouldn't have gone to the coast anyway.

144
00:14:23.780 --> 00:14:28.510
If you're worried about the invitation,
it'll be alright if I take the blame!

145
00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:30.760
If you attend the wedding, that'll be it!

146
00:14:30.760 --> 00:14:33.200
Since Mama is so used to political marriages,

147
00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:36.440
she puts bracelets on brides and grooms 
who are likely to escape.

148
00:14:36.440 --> 00:14:39.300
If you try to get off
the island with them...

149
00:14:39.300 --> 00:14:41.580
They'll explode.

150
00:14:40.840 --> 00:14:41.580
Huh?

151
00:14:45.180 --> 00:14:47.490
Your mom has the key to them.

152
00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:51.710
To get that, I'd have to defeat 
the Big Mom Pirates.

153
00:14:51.710 --> 00:14:54.010
Don't tell me Mama has already...

154
00:14:54.010 --> 00:15:00.120
Yeah, she's already made
those arrangements, and besides...

155
00:15:03.090 --> 00:15:06.340
I don't have a single ally around me.

156
00:15:13.720 --> 00:15:16.390
Even though we're related by blood...

157
00:15:21.490 --> 00:15:23.560
This is what they've done.

158
00:15:24.200 --> 00:15:28.030
Did your real family hurt you like that?

159
00:15:28.030 --> 00:15:29.250
Yeah.

160
00:15:29.650 --> 00:15:31.990
How could they...

161
00:15:32.620 --> 00:15:38.450
It seems like I'm a failure to them,
and they can't stand my existence.

162
00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:44.150
I've never even once thought
that I was happy to be born royal.

163
00:15:47.760 --> 00:15:50.610
That's why I set out to sea...

164
00:15:51.130 --> 00:15:54.470
to find a place I wasn't even sure existed.

165
00:15:56.020 --> 00:15:57.100
But...

166
00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:02.870
if I resist the marriage,

167
00:16:04.560 --> 00:16:07.610
my friends and I will be all dead.

168
00:16:07.610 --> 00:16:09.320
On top of that,

169
00:16:09.320 --> 00:16:15.450
they'll kill my real father in the East Blue,
a man I'm deeply indebted to!

170
00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:20.450
Wherever I look, I have no way out.

171
00:16:20.910 --> 00:16:22.220
So...

172
00:16:23.890 --> 00:16:26.540
I decided to stop resisting!

173
00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:35.580
On the condition that I accept this marriage,

174
00:16:35.580 --> 00:16:38.760
I want Big Mom to let my friends go.

175
00:16:43.520 --> 00:16:46.600
They're going after Luffy and the others.

176
00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:50.230
I'm sorry!

177
00:16:50.230 --> 00:16:54.070
My mother put you 
in such a difficult position!

178
00:16:54.750 --> 00:16:56.210
Stop!

179
00:16:56.210 --> 00:16:58.620
It's not your fault!

180
00:16:58.620 --> 00:16:59.530
But...

181
00:17:02.680 --> 00:17:08.060
Thirteen years ago... I was in hell.

182
00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:11.160
Now I'm back in it.

183
00:17:11.740 --> 00:17:17.090
I should be happy to have been away
from here as long as 13 years.

184
00:17:17.090 --> 00:17:20.680
The people who let me
polish my cooking skills

185
00:17:20.680 --> 00:17:23.890
and the friends who I traveled with...

186
00:17:24.990 --> 00:17:28.810
I'm indebted to everyone that I met.

187
00:17:29.450 --> 00:17:32.480
I just wanna go away without hurting anyone.

188
00:17:34.460 --> 00:17:38.030
My adventure ends here.

189
00:17:43.920 --> 00:17:48.920
Hey, don't cry.
It makes me feel pathetic!

190
00:17:49.750 --> 00:17:51.570
I...

191
00:17:55.100 --> 00:17:56.760
Sanji-san !

192
00:17:57.760 --> 00:18:02.600
I won't let your marriage with me be hell!

193
00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:16.110
I'm sorry! What am I saying?!
You're deeply suffering!

194
00:18:16.110 --> 00:18:20.280
The unwanted marriage
should be hell to you, too!

195
00:18:20.280 --> 00:18:23.240
How could I say such a thing
when someone's in pain?!

196
00:18:23.240 --> 00:18:25.830
I'm ashamed of myself! I'm sorry!

197
00:18:25.830 --> 00:18:32.130
I've only known you for a short time!
There's no way I can fill the hole in your heart!

198
00:18:32.130 --> 00:18:37.620
In the first place, you didn't even say
that you're gonna marry me!

199
00:18:37.620 --> 00:18:39.300
I'm so...

200
00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:14.670
You're my... salvation.

201
00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:18.210
Sanji-san...

202
00:19:19.170 --> 00:19:22.140
If I'm good enough for you...

203
00:19:23.840 --> 00:19:27.440
Let's get married tomorrow.

204
00:19:34.150 --> 00:19:36.340
<b>Outside Sweet City</b>

205
00:19:36.320 --> 00:19:38.820
Thanks for all the damage.

206
00:19:39.710 --> 00:19:41.150
What is this?!

207
00:19:41.800 --> 00:19:43.490
Get down here!

208
00:19:54.150 --> 00:19:55.700
I wasn't paying attention.

209
00:19:55.700 --> 00:20:01.550
I didn't expect that a girl like you could
make such a big lightning strike.

210
00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:36.290
The named blade...

211
00:20:38.350 --> 00:20:40.050
Shirauo.

212
00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:44.300
It's not what you think!
We didn't mean to change sides!

213
00:20:46.090 --> 00:20:47.850
Lady Amande!

214
00:20:50.310 --> 00:20:53.430
Slow Ballad!

215
00:21:03.900 --> 00:21:06.930
Ouch...!

216
00:21:06.930 --> 00:21:11.580
I-If you're going to kill
me, d-do it quickly!

217
00:21:13.910 --> 00:21:18.610
It's pointless killing someone quickly.

218
00:21:18.610 --> 00:21:23.880
I cut at the most painful
and tormenting speed.

219
00:21:33.930 --> 00:21:36.500
I can't believe it, Straw Hat.

220
00:21:36.500 --> 00:21:41.520
He doesn't seem like
he was fighting Big Bro Cracker all night!

221
00:21:41.520 --> 00:21:44.150
The Chess Peacekeepers aren't that weak!

222
00:21:45.200 --> 00:21:47.930
How could he tear them to pieces like trash?!

223
00:21:50.370 --> 00:21:53.080
Now, bring it on!

224
00:22:02.840 --> 00:22:03.800
Luffy!

225
00:22:03.800 --> 00:22:07.380
Cream Monster!

226
00:22:09.010 --> 00:22:10.180
What's this?!

227
00:22:13.380 --> 00:22:14.270
Ouch!

228
00:22:14.270 --> 00:22:18.440
That's the power of fresh
cream's sweetness!

229
00:22:19.980 --> 00:22:26.150
When the sweet cream sweetens,
your whole body will be burned.

230
00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:32.530
Gum-Gum...

231
00:22:32.700 --> 00:22:36.000
Uh-uh!
That's not gonna happen, Straw Hat!

232
00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:38.540
Elephant Gun!

233
00:23:01.240 --> 00:23:03.610
What is this place?

234
00:23:24.540 --> 00:23:25.710
You're in...

235
00:23:27.030 --> 00:23:29.300
the World of Books!

236
00:23:34.010 --> 00:23:36.100
Ouch! Ow, ow, ow...

237
00:23:37.970 --> 00:23:40.690
Cream Monster!

238
00:23:47.320 --> 00:23:48.860
Luffy!

239
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:08.170
Stop it!

240
00:24:14.460 --> 00:24:16.390
Luffy! Get down!

241
00:24:16.900 --> 00:24:18.310
Nami!

242
00:24:25.520 --> 00:24:26.400
Watch out!

243
00:24:31.530 --> 00:24:33.950
Cream...

244
00:24:36.820 --> 00:24:39.100
Punch!

245
00:24:39.100 --> 00:24:41.250
Luffy!

246
00:25:03.910 --> 00:25:05.740
Kingbaum...

247
00:25:18.160 --> 00:25:23.180
I was wondering why the Chess Peacekeepers,
who are homies, couldn't fight like usual,

248
00:25:23.180 --> 00:25:27.120
and how you guys could
make it out of the forest.

249
00:25:27.120 --> 00:25:29.150
Now I understand.

250
00:25:30.090 --> 00:25:33.670
Why did you have Mama's vivre card?

251
00:25:33.670 --> 00:25:36.130
It says "Lola."

252
00:25:36.130 --> 00:25:39.200
Lola?! Did you steal it from her?!

253
00:25:39.200 --> 00:25:42.680
Oh, man! That runaway girl got killed?!

254
00:25:42.680 --> 00:25:44.980
– Lola!
– What were her last words?!

255
00:25:44.980 --> 00:25:48.850
It's not like that!
She's my friend! She gave it to me!

256
00:25:48.850 --> 00:25:50.340
I doubt it.

257
00:25:50.340 --> 00:25:52.420
Tell Mama that yourself.

258
00:25:52.420 --> 00:25:56.030
Unfortunately, we were ordered
to catch you guys alive.

259
00:25:56.030 --> 00:25:57.110
Let's go.

260
00:25:57.480 --> 00:26:00.580
Oh, look at that.

261
00:26:00.580 --> 00:26:04.450
Most of the Chess Peacekeepers
have been beaten.

262
00:26:28.060 --> 00:26:33.070
I'll... wait... here...

263
00:26:39.310 --> 00:26:41.950
For Sanji...

264
00:26:47.110 --> 00:26:50.000
Luffy!

265
00:27:04.500 --> 00:27:08.540
<b>Whole Cake Chateau</b>

266
00:27:12.540 --> 00:27:14.330
R-Really?!

267
00:27:14.330 --> 00:27:17.190
Yes, really.

268
00:27:17.190 --> 00:27:23.250
When it comes to reasonable deals,
I'm a reasonable person!

269
00:27:23.250 --> 00:27:25.340
I'll let all members of the Straw Hats,

270
00:27:25.340 --> 00:27:29.560
who are your friends at this time,
leave this island alive!

271
00:27:29.560 --> 00:27:32.420
I promise.

272
00:27:33.290 --> 00:27:39.190
If you drop the idea of running away,
and marry without resistance,

273
00:27:39.190 --> 00:27:42.390
I'll turn a blind eye to everything!

274
00:27:42.390 --> 00:27:47.180
I appreciate it!
I'll make Pudding-chan happy at any cost!

275
00:27:50.160 --> 00:27:57.190
Oh, so you're in love with my daughter!
I'm glad!

276
00:28:00.110 --> 00:28:02.420
Listen.

277
00:28:02.420 --> 00:28:09.830
The things that the Straw Hats have done to me
are normally inexcusable.

278
00:28:12.120 --> 00:28:18.500
They destroyed the Seducing Woods
and took down one of our sweet commanders.

279
00:28:18.500 --> 00:28:23.870
On top of that, on Fishman Island,
not only did they eat my candies,

280
00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:26.470
but they also picked a fight with me.

281
00:28:29.930 --> 00:28:35.210
But right now, our top priority
is the marriage between you and Pudding.

282
00:28:35.210 --> 00:28:37.230
If things go well,

283
00:28:37.230 --> 00:28:42.440
about this time tomorrow,
I'll gain Germa's military strength,

284
00:28:42.440 --> 00:28:50.820
and we'll all have a delicious wedding cake!

285
00:28:50.820 --> 00:28:58.290
As long as you don't try to run away, 
everything will work out just fine, Sanji.

286
00:28:58.290 --> 00:29:00.210
Yeah!

287
00:29:12.930 --> 00:29:15.940
It is said that

288
00:29:15.880 --> 00:29:21.920
<b>Treasure Repository, Whole Cake Chateau</b>

289
00:29:15.940 --> 00:29:18.020
there are inscribed stone blocks

290
00:29:18.020 --> 00:29:20.110
that have never broken

291
00:29:20.110 --> 00:29:21.890
over the course of hundreds of years...

292
00:29:21.890 --> 00:29:25.320
They are known as poneglyphs, totaling 30,

293
00:29:25.320 --> 00:29:28.660
and are spread 
throughout the whole world-bon !

294
00:29:31.750 --> 00:29:38.540
And only nine of those 30 poneglyphs
have specific kinds of information.

295
00:29:39.040 --> 00:29:43.620
If you take those to the
last island, Laugh Tale,

296
00:29:43.620 --> 00:29:49.050
the stones will reveal the
truth of this world-soir.

297
00:29:51.350 --> 00:29:54.520
Please don't do it,
Sweet Commander Smoothie!

298
00:29:54.520 --> 00:29:56.810
Please! Please!

299
00:29:56.810 --> 00:29:59.730
Have mercy on me, Mistress Smoothie!

300
00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:11.490
Mistress Smoothie...

301
00:30:14.120 --> 00:30:20.910
But, in order to go 
to the last island Laugh Tale, you need...

302
00:30:20.910 --> 00:30:24.670
the four lode poneglyphs, the red stones!

303
00:30:24.670 --> 00:30:29.470
Including the one delivered
by Jinbe the other day...

304
00:30:29.470 --> 00:30:32.720
A present for you. I got it on my way here.

305
00:30:32.720 --> 00:30:34.270
It's from me, too!

306
00:30:34.270 --> 00:30:40.190
...we Big Mom Pirates have two poneglyphs

307
00:30:40.190 --> 00:30:43.190
and one lode poneglyph.

308
00:30:43.190 --> 00:30:47.900
That means three stones in total-vous plaît.

309
00:30:48.740 --> 00:30:52.620
I know how important those three stones are.

310
00:30:54.870 --> 00:30:56.500
But,

311
00:30:56.500 --> 00:31:01.200
why the sudden tightening of security, Tamago?

312
00:30:56.780 --> 00:31:01.560
<b>One of the Big Mom Pirates'
Three Sweet Commanders
(and the Minister of Juice)</b>

313
00:31:01.200 --> 00:31:03.660
I've got nothing to do until the tea party,

314
00:31:01.780 --> 00:31:06.780
<b>Charlotte Smoothie
14th Daughter of the Charlotte Family
Bounty: 932 Million Belly</b>

315
00:31:03.660 --> 00:31:06.780
so I don't mind guarding them.

316
00:31:06.840 --> 00:31:11.010
Yes, thank you-renaissance.

317
00:31:11.010 --> 00:31:17.220
There is a former pirate captain
who came to this island about five years ago.

318
00:31:17.220 --> 00:31:21.960
He is a mink poneglyph thief,
and it seems that

319
00:31:21.960 --> 00:31:26.110
he has snuck onto this island again-soufflé.

320
00:31:26.110 --> 00:31:27.100
Oh, no!

321
00:31:27.100 --> 00:31:32.220
His life was spared because his
compatriot Pekoms begged for his life.

322
00:31:32.220 --> 00:31:35.200
Why did he return?

323
00:31:37.200 --> 00:31:39.270
Pedro!

324
00:31:41.500 --> 00:31:49.300
If you get all four red lode poneglyphs,
you can reach Laugh Tale.

325
00:31:49.300 --> 00:31:52.860
In other words, that's the road
to become king of the pirates!

326
00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:57.810
That's a quest worthy 
of the Four Emperors-bon.

327
00:32:00.850 --> 00:32:09.110
For the sake of Mama, we put our lives on
the line to protect these stones-chocolat !

328
00:32:14.940 --> 00:32:18.470
<b>Outside the Treasure Repository, Whole Cake Chateau</b>

329
00:32:22.210 --> 00:32:23.490
Brook.

330
00:32:26.450 --> 00:32:29.050
<b>Spirits Cellar</b>

331
00:32:29.050 --> 00:32:31.970
What? They increased security?

332
00:32:31.970 --> 00:32:36.750
Yes, they were calling her
"Sweet Commander Smoothie."

333
00:32:36.750 --> 00:32:39.600
Sweet commander... 
That means she's a top officer!

334
00:32:39.930 --> 00:32:43.980
I thought so.
No wonder she looked strong.

335
00:32:43.980 --> 00:32:48.300
It's hopeless.
They now have perfect security.

336
00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:51.050
There's no chance even at night.

337
00:32:52.540 --> 00:32:57.670
Our last hope may have vanished
when Tamago noticed I was here.

338
00:32:57.670 --> 00:33:00.690
Luffy and the others are having difficulty.

339
00:33:00.690 --> 00:33:04.080
It'd be nice if we could
complete our mission smoothly.

340
00:33:04.420 --> 00:33:10.210
I was touched by what you said the other day.

341
00:33:11.890 --> 00:33:15.140
In order for Luffy-san to become

342
00:33:15.140 --> 00:33:19.810
king of the pirates, 
he'll eventually need that lode poneglyph.

343
00:33:19.810 --> 00:33:24.810
But it won't be so easy to come back here.

344
00:33:25.140 --> 00:33:30.980
Rather, we have to clash with them head-on
if we really want to come back.

345
00:33:30.980 --> 00:33:33.990
I don't think we all could
make it this far again.

346
00:33:35.080 --> 00:33:36.570
That's right.

347
00:33:36.570 --> 00:33:41.200
Given this, maybe now is the rare chance.

348
00:33:43.410 --> 00:33:47.670
But if we invade, both of us will get killed!

349
00:33:48.750 --> 00:33:51.640
Who is Baron Tamago's target?

350
00:33:51.640 --> 00:33:53.250
It's me.

351
00:34:02.510 --> 00:34:04.520
Pedro-san,

352
00:34:04.520 --> 00:34:07.230
would you be
willing to serve as bait?

353
00:34:10.200 --> 00:34:14.320
That's exactly what I was thinking.
